    "text": "If stars ever fell?\nCurated by Ishmail De Niro\n\n‘…I wanted to reflect upon artists I have known in a past life, or artists, now, who I desperately want to know. Why does art appeal to us? What problems does it solve? What lessons does it teach? How does it make us feel?’\n\nFeaturing works from Umar Ahmed, Baesianz, the estate of Shah Jahan, Poppy Nash, and Sue Tompkins.\n\nIllustration by Ivy Vo with graphics by Ishmail De Niro.",
